{"TopicId":183691,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Environment-friendly encapsulated RTG","CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-13T09:50:26Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-13T09:50:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn 1967 they were designing a military version of \u003Cem\u003ESoyuz\u003C/em\u003E, \u003Cem\u003ESoyuz-VI\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 (\u0022VI\u0022 is not \u00226th\u0022, its \u0022/ve/ /i:/\u0022, after \u0022military explorer\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstead of solar panels which can fail, it was using two \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E set on long foldable external trusses.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnlike us, they worried about the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E burning in the atmosphere (especially due\u00A0to the nuclear tests treaty), so in the late design the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E were put into their own small reentry capsules, to be found by the rescue team after landing,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a shame that we are still burning \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E in the Kerbin atmosphere. It would be a nice practice to keep implementing this solution in the name of Green Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-04-13T09:51:51Z\u0022 title=\u002204/13/2019 09:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EApril 13, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-13T16:20:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223582177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022183691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221555149027\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a shame that we are still burning \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E in the Kerbin atmosphere.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmaybe some kerbs are - but not us!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4123360391\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/KSA_MissionCtrl/status/1108430254165520384\u0022 style=\u0022height:243px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2166582508\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/KSA_MissionCtrl/status/1108430755